PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F392A1733299890
OL,3,C"He acted so brazenly, not caring that
OL,4,Che could be caught."
OL,6,F"Had the defendant been driving at
OL,7,F30mph, Mrs Howe would have had ample
OL,8,Ftime to complete her turn without the
OL,9,Fdefendant taking any action," the
OL,10,Fprosecutor added.
OL,12,FThe VW Polo collided with the Toyota
OL,13,FAygo sending both cars spinning across
OL,14,Fthe junction. Mrs Howe was seriously
OL,15,Finjured. Nearby builders used angle
OL,16,Fgrinders and crowbars to get her out
OL,17,Fof the car. She and her husband were
OL,18,Frushed to hospital.
