OL,3,C"He acted so brazenly, not caring that
OL,4,Che could be caught."
OL,6,FThe barrister said he was diagnosed
OL,7,Fwith ADHD which reflected in him
OL,8,F'acting like a teenager'.
OL,10,FJudge Angela Nield, sentencing,
OL,11,Fdescribed Mansfield-Marr's driving as
OL,12,F'frankly appalling', and said: "This
OL,13,Fwas not a one off but a habit, and a
OL,14,Fhabit to be celebrated on social
OL,15,Fmedia. It was a matter of pride."
OL,17,FMansfield-Marr, of St Paul's Gardens,
OL,18,Fwas jailed for 12 years and banned
OL,19,Ffrom driving for 16 years. He will
OL,20,Fserve two thirds of the jail term
OL,21,Fbefore being released on licence.
